<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. Elytral punctures and coloration: a in rows in deep striae, Pachybrachis luctuosus b confused in basal half, in rows in apical half, Pachybrachis calcaratus c all confused, Pachybrachis hepaticus d confused and mottled, Pachybrachis spumarius e vittate with marginal vitta interrupted, Pachybrachis bivattatus f black, margined with yellow, Pachybrachis nigriconis carbonarius g entirely black, Pachybrachis luridus." , "Habitus 5. Dorsal habitus of Pachybrachis hepaticus hepaticus. Scale bar, 1 mm." , "Figure 3. Front femora: a not enlarged, Pachybrachis hepaticus b thickened, Pachybrachis peccans." , "Map 5. The known distribution of Pachybrachis hepaticus hepaticus in eastern Canada. OL - Ontario Lake; OR - Ottawa River." , "Figure 1. Eyes: a close eyes, Pachybrachis pectoralis b normal eyes, Pachybrachis peccans c normal eyes and yellow face, male Pachybrachis atomarius d remote eyes, Pachybrachis hepaticus." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20912" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20858" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20860" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20864" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20937" .

